        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 3:28PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles southwest of Kim, or 27 miles northeast of Des Moines, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kim, Open county along and south of highway 160.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
